Thoughtly privacy policy
Privacy Policy
Last Updated: March 9, 2025
Harshita App Tech built the
Thoughtly
app as an ad-supported service. This
Privacy Policy
explains how we collect, use, and protect your information when you use our services. By using
Thoughtly
, you agree to the collection and use of information in accordance with this policy.
1. Information We Collect
1.1 Personal Information
We may require you to provide certain personally identifiable information for an improved experience. This may include, but is not limited to:
Name
Email address
User-generated content
Note:
The app retains this data on your device, and we do not store or collect it directly.
1.2 Automatically Collected Data (Log Data)
Whenever you use our service, we may collect
Log Data
through third-party services. This may include:
Device Internet Protocol (IP) address
Device name and model
Operating system version
App usage statistics
Time and date of service access
1.3 Cookies & Tracking Technologies
Thoughtly does not explicitly use
cookies
. However, third-party services integrated into the app may use cookies to enhance functionality. You can manage your cookie preferences through your device settings.
2. Third-Party Services
We may use third-party services to provide essential app functionality. These services may collect information to improve their features. Below are the third-party services we use:
Google Play Services
AdMob (for advertisements)
Google Analytics for Firebase
(for user behavior tracking)
Firebase Crashlytics
(for app crash reporting)
We encourage users to review the privacy policies of these third parties for more details.
3. How We Use Your Information
We use the collected data to:
Provide, maintain, and improve the Thoughtly app
Personalize user experiences
Monitor app performance and fix issues
Serve relevant advertisements
We do not sell or share your personal data with third parties beyond what is necessary to provide and improve the service.
4. Security Measures
We prioritize protecting your personal information and implement industry-standard security measures. However, please note that no method of transmission over the internet is
100% secure
, and we cannot guarantee absolute security.
5. Childrenâ€™s Privacy
The Thoughtly app is
not intended for children under 13 years of age
. We do not knowingly collect personal data from children. If you believe a child has provided us with personal information, please contact us immediately so we can take appropriate action.
6. User Rights & Data Control
Under various data protection laws (such as GDPR and CCPA), users have rights regarding their personal information, including:
Access & Correction:
You can request a copy of your personal data and correct inaccuracies.
Data Deletion:
You can request that we delete any personal data associated with you.
Opt-Out of Ads & Tracking:
You can disable personalized ads via your Google account settings or third-party service settings.
To exercise any of these rights, please contact us at
help@thoughtly.cloud
.
7. Links to Other Sites
The Thoughtly app may contain links to third-party websites. We are
not responsible
for their privacy practices. We encourage you to read their privacy policies before sharing any information.
8. Safety Standards & Child Sexual Abuse Material (CSAM) Policy
We are committed to ensuring a safe environment for all users and strictly prohibit the use of
Thoughtly
for sharing or distributing
child sexual abuse and exploitation (CSAE/CSAM) content
.
Posting, sharing, or distributing CSAE/CSAM is
strictly prohibited
and is a violation of
Google's Terms of Service
.
Thoughtly does not provide, host, or store
any such material. Content is hosted by the operators of the servers you interact with.
If you encounter CSAM on a server, please
report it directly to the operators of that server
.
Reports should NOT be made to Thoughtly developers
, as we are unable to take action on external content.
If you need to notify us regarding safety concerns, please contact us at
team@thoughtly.cloud
.
For more information on our safety policies, please visit:
RAINN | The nation's largest anti-sexual violence organization
9. Changes to This Privacy Policy
We may update this Privacy Policy periodically. Any changes will be posted on this page, and users are encouraged to review this policy from time to time.
